article.headline: Loyola of Chicago 61, Cleveland St. 57
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- J.R. Blount scored 27 points, including four 3-pointers, and Loyola of Chicago overcame a second half surge by Cleveland State to beat the Vikings 61-57 Thursday night. The Ramblers (15-9, 6-5 Horizon League) took a 37-21 lead into the second half but Cleveland State (8-16, 2-9) went on a 24-8 run to tie the game with 7:09 left. Loyola then pulled ahead by six before Bahaadar Russell hit a 3-pointer for Cleveland State to tie it 53-53 with less than three minutes on the clock. Loyola scored its final eight points on free throws, seven shot by Blount, while holding the Vikings to two baskets. Blake Schilb scored 13 for the Ramblers, who shot about 36 percent (20-of-56). Renard Fields came off the bench to lead Cleveland State with 12 points and 16 rebounds. Joe Davis scored 12, and Russell added 11. The Vikings shot about 30 percent (20-of-66) and never held the lead.
